Break is used in "if" loop the same way like in switch to prematurely break the operation.
The break stops the loop once the condition is met
Why we use break:
    If we use break we can save a lot of unnecessary processing by terminating
    the loop once the goal is complete.
Continue:
    Is used to skin unnecessary calculations. If an element meets a condition that element
    is skipped and we move to next element.

   Note: Break and continue keyword are always used in the if loop
   Continue skips iterations that don't match the if loop condition.

   2D array:
   2D array is simply multiple one D arrays combined together in the form of rows and columns;
